So the next app I want to show you is a comorbidity or a

00:26:59.040 --> 00:27:03.719
multimorbidity analysis app. Now, as I said, a comorbidity

00:27:03.719 --> 00:27:07.880
is two diseases. So if you have two diseases, it's comorbidities

00:27:08.199 --> 00:27:10.040
that you have. If you have more than two diseases, it's

00:27:10.040 --> 00:27:15.319
multimorbidities. And the figure on the left, it shows you that

00:27:16.000 --> 00:27:20.280
if you have a heart condition, or if you have cancer, then your

00:27:20.280 --> 00:27:24.079
life expectancy tends to decrease by the number of

00:27:24.119 --> 00:27:27.839
additional health conditions you have. So if you only had a heart

00:27:27.880 --> 00:27:30.920
disease, your life expectancy after you first got heart

00:27:30.920 --> 00:27:34.760
disease was say 20 years. Every additional disease, if you got

00:27:34.760 --> 00:27:38.920
diabetes along with it, then it'll start decreasing your life

00:27:38.920 --> 00:27:43.479
expectancy. And on average, your life expectancy decreases by two

00:27:43.479 --> 00:27:46.680
years for every additional condition you have. So if you

00:27:46.680 --> 00:27:50.000
only had heart condition, and now you've also got diabetes,

00:27:50.040 --> 00:27:54.199
then your life expectancy just decreased by on average 1.8

00:27:54.199 --> 00:27:56.359
years for every additional condition you have. So

00:27:56.359 --> 00:28:01.400
multimorbidities are costly. And comorbidities are costly. In

00:28:01.400 --> 00:28:03.839
fact, we also looked at our own internal data and we found the

00:28:03.839 --> 00:28:07.959
same trend. The more diseases you have, the more number of

00:28:07.959 --> 00:28:10.800
additional diseases you have, the more costly you get in the

00:28:10.800 --> 00:28:14.839
next one year for us. And obviously, for us, our main

00:28:14.839 --> 00:28:17.839
goal is to make our members healthy and save money in the

00:28:17.839 --> 00:28:23.040
process. So trying to find this population, trying to figure out

00:28:23.040 --> 00:28:25.439
what are the most common multimorbidities and what are

00:28:25.439 --> 00:28:28.000
the most expensive multimorbidities, what are the

00:28:28.000 --> 00:28:32.439
most impactable multimorbidities is very, very central to our

00:28:32.439 --> 00:28:38.000
whole business. Now, the analysis I'll show you uses

00:28:38.000 --> 00:28:42.000
something called market basket analysis, or association rules.

00:28:42.520 --> 00:28:46.000
People in retail are must be familiar with this analysis.

00:28:46.040 --> 00:28:50.280
Essentially, what it is, is if you had these, if you've, if

00:28:50.280 --> 00:28:54.560
you're sitting at Walmart, at the cashier's register, and you

00:28:54.560 --> 00:28:58.319
see people make these different transactions. So in the first

00:28:58.319 --> 00:29:02.920
transaction, they bought an apple, a beer, cocaine or

00:29:02.920 --> 00:29:06.680
sugar, I'm not sure what and then meat. And these are the

00:29:06.680 --> 00:29:10.199
different transactions that they had, then you can calculate

00:29:10.199 --> 00:29:14.400
three essential metrics. The first is support. So four out of

00:29:14.400 --> 00:29:18.359
the eight transaction contained an apple, so the support is

00:29:18.359 --> 00:29:24.599
0.5. If then you can also define confidence, that is the people

00:29:24.599 --> 00:29:28.760
who bought an apple and a beer among the total number of people

00:29:28.760 --> 00:29:33.199
who bought an apple. So here, you would just try to find how

00:29:33.199 --> 00:29:35.640
many people who bought an apple also bought a beer. So that is

00:29:35.640 --> 00:29:40.160
a confidence. And finally lift is just how much more likely are

00:29:40.160 --> 00:29:44.680
you to buy a beer if you bought an apple. And if you have a lift

00:29:44.680 --> 00:29:47.199
greater than one, that that means there is a positive

00:29:47.199 --> 00:29:49.479
association. So you're more likely to buy an apple if you

00:29:49.479 --> 00:29:53.560
bought beer. And if a lift of left less than one is negative

00:29:53.560 --> 00:29:57.319
association, that is you're less likely to buy it. Now, you might

00:29:57.319 --> 00:29:59.800
have heard of stories where they've used association rules

00:29:59.800 --> 00:30:06.400
like diapers are now kept with beer. And it's because

00:30:06.400 --> 00:30:09.839
association rules show that people on I think Tuesday or

00:30:09.839 --> 00:30:13.199
Wednesday night, they tend to go out to Walmart, and they look

00:30:13.239 --> 00:30:17.920
they will buy beer with diapers more likely these are parents

00:30:17.920 --> 00:30:19.640
who are just trying to get a diaper and they'll be like, okay,

00:30:19.640 --> 00:30:24.199
I need a beer too. And so these are used either they put the

00:30:24.239 --> 00:30:28.079
things together, or they might put them on opposite ends of the

00:30:28.079 --> 00:30:30.959
store. So if you go to Walmart, if they found out that you need

00:30:31.199 --> 00:30:35.199
Apple, if you need beer and diapers, they'll put beer at the

00:30:35.199 --> 00:30:38.359
front of the store and diapers at the very back. So then you

00:30:38.359 --> 00:30:40.599
will walk through the whole store and buy more things. So

00:30:40.599 --> 00:30:44.719
that's how they use association rules in retail. Now you can

00:30:44.760 --> 00:30:49.760
employ this the same logic in healthcare as well. You can

00:30:49.760 --> 00:30:53.880
define support as the number of people who have disease one and

00:30:53.880 --> 00:30:57.839
disease two overall. So if you have 100 patients, how many of

00:30:57.839 --> 00:31:01.959
them have hypertension and diabetes? Confidence is how many

00:31:01.959 --> 00:31:05.439
people who have the two diseases divided by the number of people

00:31:05.439 --> 00:31:09.199
who have the disease of your interest. So of the people who

00:31:09.199 --> 00:31:13.239
are diabetic, how many of them also have hypertension? And the

00:31:13.239 --> 00:31:17.199
lift is just then how much more likely are you to have

00:31:17.359 --> 00:31:20.479
hypertension if you already had diabetes, if your lift is more

00:31:20.479 --> 00:31:23.000
than one, then you're more likely if it is less than one,

00:31:23.000 --> 00:31:28.239
you're less likely. And so this is a paper that that uses

00:31:28.239 --> 00:31:31.680
association rules for comorbidity analysis. And there

00:31:31.680 --> 00:31:33.880
have been a lot of different papers that have used it

00:31:33.880 --> 00:31:38.000
including myself, I published some research on using

