Alright, so propensity score matching app, as I said,

00:38:13.399 --> 00:38:17.239
propensity score matching is a is a causal inference technique.

00:38:17.280 --> 00:38:21.600
So if you do not have a randomized control trial, and

00:38:21.600 --> 00:38:24.320
you only have a treatment group and you want to estimate the

00:38:24.320 --> 00:38:27.479
average treatment effect, then you would have to find people

00:38:27.479 --> 00:38:30.520
who are who can be a synthetic control. And then you have to

00:38:30.520 --> 00:38:33.600
create for every member in the treatment group, you have to

00:38:33.600 --> 00:38:37.159
find a matching member who's very similar. And you can use

00:38:37.159 --> 00:38:41.639
him as a control. So say if a member was living in a

00:38:41.639 --> 00:38:48.000
metropolitan city, he was a middle aged male, his candy

00:38:48.000 --> 00:38:52.840
based candy crunch score was 50 in candy crunch, then you would

00:38:52.840 --> 00:38:55.760
have to find a control member who had all of those similar

00:38:58.000 --> 00:39:01.320
similar characteristics. So to do that, you use something

00:39:01.320 --> 00:39:03.719
called propensity score matching. It's a very popular

00:39:04.000 --> 00:39:05.679
technique in quasi experimental

00:39:07.159 --> 00:39:11.280
trials. And you can use this analysis to do different things,

00:39:11.280 --> 00:39:14.479
you can find baseline characteristics. I apologize if

00:39:14.479 --> 00:39:17.679
this sounds a little foreign to you. But this is more for

00:39:17.679 --> 00:39:21.919
experimental analysis for it's very useful in when you're

00:39:21.919 --> 00:39:26.479
trying to run quasi experiments. So the usual process of running

00:39:26.479 --> 00:39:28.879
these experiments is first you have to find baseline

00:39:28.879 --> 00:39:33.199
characteristics. That is, at the baseline, how much are my

00:39:33.199 --> 00:39:36.320
treatment group differ different from the control

00:39:36.320 --> 00:39:39.919
group, then you match them, you find people who are similar in

00:39:39.919 --> 00:39:42.879
the treatment, and you find matching controls. And after

00:39:42.879 --> 00:39:45.560
you found them, you try to quantify have I been able to

00:39:45.560 --> 00:39:49.800
remove all the differences that were there in before matching.

00:39:50.679 --> 00:39:52.639
And then you also sometimes perform something called the

00:39:52.639 --> 00:39:57.919
sensitivity analysis. So this is something that we, we tend to

